🧬 BLAST Analysis

BLAST (Basic Local Alignment Search Tool) was used to identify homologous sequences by comparing query DNA/protein sequences against NCBI databases. This step helps in understanding sequence similarity, evolutionary relationships, and functional annotation.

## 🛠 Tools Used
NCBI BLAST (blastn / blastp)
NCBI GenBank database
FASTA sequence format

##⚙️ Workflow
Input sequence prepared in FASTA format
Sequence submitted to NCBI BLAST
Database search performed (nr/refseq)
Top hits analyzed based on E-value, identity, and coverage

##📊 Output Interpretation
Lower E-value indicates higher significance
Higher identity % shows stronger similarity
High query coverage confirms reliable alignment

##🧠 Purpose

Results were used for identifying homologous genes/proteins and selecting candidate sequences for downstream structural modeling and molecular docking.
